  "text": "Well-organized service. SMMC recently described the development of a Microsoft Access (Microsoft, Redmond, WA) database program to organize its service. [CITATION_1] This type of program allows the tracking of all active patients throughout the hospital. This helps each pharmacist identify which patient on anticoagulants requires an assessment and a care plan. Such data organization systems can also be designed to track the workload of the service for justifi cation reasons.",
